%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgolden-age-gig-work-instacart-doordash-delivery-jobs-over-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egig%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20took%20effect%20on%20Jan.%2013.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20Instacart%20shopper%20said%20that%20the%20law%20has%20created%C2%A0%26quot%3Ba%20livable%20wage%26quot%3B%20for%20workers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20other%20issues%2C%20like%20sudden%20%26quot%3Bdeactivations%26quot%3B%2C%20need%20more%20attention%2C%20the%20shopper%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Michelle%20Balzer%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstacart-shopper-works-18-hour-days-road-trips-cities-orders-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ean%20Instacart%20driver%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20in%20Seattle.%20Balzer%20was%20among%20those%20who%20advocated%20for%20PayUp%2C%20a%20series%20of%20bills%20meant%20to%20protect%20gig%20workers%20passed%20by%20Seattle's%20city%20council.%20One%20of%20the%20laws%2C%20which%20requires%20companies%20like%20Instacart%20to%20pay%20contractors%20the%20equivalent%20of%20the%20city's%20%2419.97-an-hour%20minimum%20wage%2C%20took%20effect%20on%20January%2013.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Insider%20has%20verified%20Balzer's%20employment%20and%20identity.%20The%20story%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20am%20actually%20a%20licensed%20addiction%20counselor%2C%20and%20that's%20what%20I've%20been%20doing%20since%202012.%20I%20had%20just%20left%20a%20job%20right%20around%20January%202020%20and%20was%20going%20to%20start%20a%20new%20job%2C%20but%20then%20the%20pandemic%20hit%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20agencies%20shut%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstacart-shopper-won-280000-in-arbitration-after-deactivation-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworking%20for%20Instacart%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20year%2C%20but%20I%20was%20just%20getting%20my%20feet%20wet.%20In%202021%2C%20I%20went%20all%20in.%20My%20sister%20was%20a%20foster%20mom%2C%20and%20I%20liked%20the%20flexibility%20of%20being%20able%20to%20work%20and%20spend%20time%20with%20her%20kids%20on%20my%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20involved%20in%20PayUp%20right%20away.%20I'm%20in%20a%20Facebook%20group%20for%20gig%20workers%20in%20the%20Pacific%20Northwest%2C%20and%20if%20you%20ever%20talk%20to%20people%20and%20read%20the%20posts%2C%20they're%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BDon't%20bank%20on%20this%20for%20your%20own%20employment.%26quot%3B%20I%20started%20commenting%20on%20some%20posts%20and%20got%20invited%20to%20a%20meeting%20for%20people%20organizing%20around%20PayUp.%20I'm%20kind%20of%20a%20fighter%20for%20things%20that%20are%20just%2C%20and%20so%20it%20wasn't%20hard%20to%20sell%20me%20on%20being%20part%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recognize%20the%20difficult%20position%20that%20gig%20companies%20are%20put%20in.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstacart-shoppers-say-long-drives-200-item-orders-becoming-common-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInstacart%20has%20600%2C000%20shoppers.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Can%20they%20actually%20feasibly%20pay%20600%2C000%20shoppers%20and%20bring%20them%20on%20as%20employees%3F%20I%20don't%20think%20that's%20realistic%2C%20as%20deep%20as%20their%20pockets%20are.%20But%20does%20that%20mean%20they%20get%20to%20pay%20us%20the%20equivalent%20of%20%242%20an%20hour%3F%20No.%20I%20really%20felt%20like%20there%20had%20to%20be%20some%20kind%20of%20happy%20medium.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20that%20PayUp%20has%20rolled%20out%2C%20the%20money%20that%20is%20coming%20in%20now%20is%20insane.%20The%20batch%20pay%20used%20to%20be%20%2410%2C%20and%20now%20it's%20%2490.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20tradeoffs.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstacart-shoppers-forbidden-from-giving-customers-paper-receipts-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInstacart%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20set%20the%20default%20tip%20to%200%25%20when%20customers%20check%20out%20online%20%E2%80%94%20it%20used%20to%20be%205%25.%20Shoppers%20have%20to%20get%20a%20weekly%20paycheck%20instead%20of%20cashing%20out%20their%20earnings%20instantly.%20If%20you%20are%20in%20Seattle%2C%20you%20will%20never%20be%20able%20to%20accept%20an%20order%20that%20goes%20out%20of%20Seattle's%20city%20limits.%20I%20feel%20like%20Instacart%20got%20really%20tedious%20with%20the%20rules%20and%20kind%20of%20punitive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20PayUp%20has%20started%2C%20I've%20seen%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20post%20about%20the%20crappy%20tips.%20And%20part%20of%20me%20goes%2C%20%26quot%3BTips%20are%20meant%20to%20subsidize%20income.%20You're%20getting%20a%20livable%20wage.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20that%20we%20in%20Seattle%20definitely%20paved%20the%20way%20with%20PayUp.%20Our%20goal%20now%20as%20a%20campaign%20is%20to%20go%20statewide%20and%20try%20to%20find%20someone%20to%20take%20this%20to%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20Washington%20state%20legislature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20are%20still%20problems.%20In%20January%2C%20I%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-gig-workers-are-fighting-against-sudden-account-deactivations-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeactivated%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Instacart%20because%20a%20customer%20claimed%20that%20I%20chipped%20some%20concrete%20on%20her%20driveway%20with%20my%20car.%20However%2C%20Instacart%20support%20said%20that%20once%20I%20provided%20proof%20of%20resolution%2C%20either%20with%20the%20customer%20directly%20or%20with%20my%20insurance%2C%20I'd%20be%20reactivated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20weeks%20later%2C%20my%20insurance%20emailed%20them%20to%20let%20them%20know%20this%20incident%20was%20resolved%2C%20but%20Instacart%20still%20hasn't%20reactivated