Cp%3ESadness%2C%20in%20our%20home%2C%20was%20always%20tied%20to%20words.%20How%20could%20something%20wordless%2C%20after%20all%2C%20make%20me%20feel%20sad%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20not%20that%20no%20one%20liked%20music%20at%20home.%20There%20were%2C%20of%20course%2C%20old%20Bollywood%20and%20Pakistani%20songs%2C%20as%20well%20as%20ghazals%20by%20iconic%20artists%2C%20to%20a%20certain%20extent.%20However%2C%20the%20latter%20were%20always%20appreciated%20solely%20for%20their%20lyrical%20material.%20Ghazal%20singers%20were%20often%20judged%20whenever%20they%20mispronounced%20any%20Urdu%20words.%20All%20the%20praise%20belonged%20to%20the%20poets%20alone.%20I%20remember%20once%20my%20mother%20politely%2C%20and%20rightly%2C%20told%20me%20it%20was%20really%20embarrassing%20not%20to%20remember%20the%20words%20accurately%20while%20quoting%20a%20poet.%20I%20must%20have%20forgotten%20a%20couplet%20while%20reciting%20it%20at%20a%20family%20gathering.%20In%20the%20Quranic%20tradition%2C%20the%20universe%20came%20into%20being%20after%20God%20commanded%20a%20singe%20word%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EKun%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Be.%E2%80%9D%20In%20our%20home%2C%20no%20medium%20was%20as%20considered%20as%20sacred%20as%20text%20and%20no%20other%20art%20form%20could%20be%20taken%20as%20seriously%20as%20poetry.%20However%2C%20this%20was%20about%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20early%20morning%20in%202002%20%E2%80%94%20when%20I%20was%2013%20%E2%80%94%20I%20met%20something%20new.%20It%20was%20as%20if%20a%20new%20language%20opened%20her%20warm%20embrace%20for%20me.%20She%20carried%20an%20unknown%20melancholia%2C%20intertwined%20with%20an%20otherworldly%20pleasure.%20I%20heard%20a%20random%20old%20Hindi%20song%20on%20TV.%20The%20song%20deeply%20saddened%20me%2C%20as%20if%20it%20had%20broken%20something%20inside%20me.%20The%20haunting%20sadness%20was%20not%20linked%20to%20the%20song%E2%80%99s%20lyrics.%20By%20this%20time%2C%20thanks%20to%20my%20childhood%20friend%2C%20the%20little%20Casi