MIE%2C%20India%20has%20failed%20to%20reap%20benefits%20of%20%E2%80%98demographic%20dividend%E2%80%99%20as%20the%20young%20population%20is%20feeling%20discouraged%20to%20even%20look%20for%20jobs.%20From%202017%20to%202022%2C%20the%20overall%20labour%20participation%20rate%20(active%20workforce%20seeking%20employment%20or%20already%20employed)%20plunged%20from%2046%25%20to%2040%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELack%20of%20jobs%20in%20the%20formal%20sector%20has%20forced%20vast%20sections%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20youth%20to%20look%20for%20opportunities%20in%20the%20precarious%20and%20unregulated%20informal%20sector.%20The%20government%E2%80%99s%20feeble%20measures%20to%20provide%20easy%20loans%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98startups%E2%80%99%20belittles%20the%20enormity%20of%20the%20unemployment%20and%20underemployment%20crisis%20facing%20the%20country.%20Nor%20does%20it%20address%20the%20question%20of%20lack%20of%20labour%20protections%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98gig%20economy%E2%80%99%2C%20where%20a%20number%20of%20young%20people%20work%20on%20meagre%20returns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKey%20schemes%20for%20the%20poor%20and%20women%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20poor%2C%20the%20finance%20minister%20speaks%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Esabka%20saath%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20approach%2C%20but%20allocates%20grossly%20insufficient%20amounts%20to%20key%20programmes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Social%20Assistance%20Programme%20(NSAP)%20witnesses%20a%20meagre%2016%20crore%20increase%2C%20with%20the%20budget%20inching%20up%20from%20Rs%209%2C636%20crore%20(BE%202023-2024)%20to%20Rs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiabudget.gov.in%2Fdoc%2FBudget_at_Glance%2Fbudget_at_a_glance.pdf%5C%22%3E9%2C652%20crore%20(BE%202024-2025)%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20last%20revision%20in%20the%20amount%20disbursed%20per%20individual%20happened%20in%202007%2C%20and%2016%20years%20later%2C%20it%20still%20stands%20at%20Rs%20200%20crore.%20Even%20a%20simple%20inflation%20adjustment%20has%20not%20been%20done%20to%20this%20paltry%20sum%2C%20which%20would%20have%20amounted%20to%20Rs%20618.09%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Act%20(NREGA)%20allocation%20shows%20no%20increase%2C%20remaining%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiabudget.gov.in%2Fdoc%2FBudget_at_Glance%2Fbudget_at_a_glance.pdf%5C%22%3ERs%2086%2C000%20crores%3C%2Fa%3E%20(BE%202024-2025)%2C%20which%20was%20the%20revised%20estimate%20for%20the%20year%202023-2024%2C%20initially%20estimated%20at%20a%20low%20of%20Rs%2060%2C000%20crore.%20On%20top%20of%20that%20only%20to%20the%20state%20of%20West%20Bengal%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20owes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1057201%2Fstruggling-to-buy-even-soap-bengal-mnrega-workers-waiting-for-wages-being-pushed-into-poverty%5C%22%3ERs%207%2C000%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20%E2%80%9Cnon-compliance%20of%20directives%E2%80%9D.%20This%20amount%20includes%20Rs%202%2C800%20crore%20of%20wage%20liabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmidst%20the%20rhetoric%20surrounding%20women%20and%20Nari%20Shakti%2C%20the%20Integrated%20Child%20Development%20Services%20(ICDS)%2C%20rebranded%20as%20Saksham%20Anganwadi%20%26amp%3B%20POSHAN%202.0%20in%20the%20fiscal%20year%202021-22%2C%20has%20witnessed%20a%20gradual%20decline%20in%20its%20budget.%20In%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbgaindia.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F03%2FFinal-RUB.pdf%5C%22%3EFY%202014-15%20(Actuals)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20budget%20allocated%20to%20ICDS%20alone%20stood%20at%20Rs%2016%2C683.6%20crore%2C%20in%20contrast%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiabudget.gov.in%2Fdoc%2FBudget_at_Glance%2Fbudget_at_a_glance.pdf%5C%22%3ERs%2021%2C220%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E%20allocated%20for%20Saksham%20Anganwadi%20%26amp%3B%20POSHAN%202.0%20in%20the%20current%20budget%2C%20covering%20three%20schemes%20%E2%80%93%20Anganwadi%20Services%2C%20Poshan%20Abhiyan%2C%20and%20Scheme%20for%20Adolescent%20Girl.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20much-touted%20128th%20Constitutional%20Amendment%20Bill%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewindiasamachar.pib.gov.in%2FWriteReadData%2Fstory%2F2023%2FOct%2FS2023101616086.pdf%5C%22%3ENari%20Shakti%20Vandan%20Adhiniyam%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20implemented%2C%20with%20delimitation%20deferred%20until%20the%20post-2026%20Census.%20This%20delay%20postpones%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20reserving%20one-third%20of%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20legislative%20assemblies.%20The%20procrastination%20of%20the%20caste%20census%20and%20delimitation%20also%20remains%20in%20the%20future%2C%20and%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20claims%20rely%20solely%20on%20announcements%2C%20lacking%20real%20implementation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20claim%20of%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20women%20participating%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublications.azimpremjiuniversity.edu.in%2F5166%2F1%2FState_of_Working_India_2023_ebook_revised.pdf%5C%22%3Elabour%20force%20%3C%2Fa%3Epaints%20a%20positive%20picture%2C%20it%20deliberately%20fails%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20this%20rise%2C%20post-pandemic%2C%20has%20compelled%20women%20to%20often%20resort%20to%20tedious%20and%20low-paid%20work%20or%20self%20employment%20due%20to%20unemployment%20and%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Frising-female-work-participation-signals-stressed-livelihoods-not-progress%5C%22%3ERising%20Female%20Work%20Participation%20Signals%20Stressed%20Livelihoods%2C%20Not%20Progress%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20exercise%20in%20diversion%20before%20the%20elections%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20interim%20budget%20showcases%20the%20skill%20of%20the%20government%20to%20remain%20unfazed%20in%20the%20face%20of%20a%20grim%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20context%20where%20wages%20of%20construction%20and%20agricultural%20workers%20have%20significantly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fif-there-was-political-will-indias-raging-cost-of-living-crisis-could-be-eased%5C%22%3Elagged%3C%2Fa%3E%20behind%20rising%20food%20prices%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Frural-income-stress-cloud-over-fmcg-demand%5C%22%3Estress%20in%20rural%20areas%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20led%20to%20a%20concerning%20decline%20in%20demand%2C%20the%20finance%20minister%E2%80%99s%20assertions%20about%20%E2%80%9Cmoderate%20inflation%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cincreased%20real%20income%20in%20rural%20areas%E2%80%9D%20can%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20deliberate%20denial%20of%20the%20cost-of-living%20crisis.%20This%20crisis%20has%20significantly%20impacted%20the%20finances%20of%20the%20common%20people%2C%20leading%20to%20gross%20savings%20of%20Indian%20households%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findia-inflation-household-financial-savings-30-year-low%5C%22%3Ehitting%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20multi-decade%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20claim%20that%20%E2%80%9Cpeople%20are%20living%20better%20and%20earning%20better%E2%80%9D%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20price%20of%20home-cooked%20meals%20has%20increased%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fdata%2Fdata-the-cost-of-meals-rose-by-65-percent-in-five-years-but-wages-by-just-37-percent%2Farticle67251257.ece%5C%22%3E65%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20last%20five%20years%20and%20our%20Global%20Hunger%20Index%20ranking%20has%20slipped%20further%20down%20sounds%20a%20wishful%20distortion%20of%20reality.%20The%20budget%20has%20made%20misleading%20claims%2C%20such%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Caverage%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D2001085%5C%22%3Ereal%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20people%20has%20increased%20by%2050%25%E2%80%9D.%20In%20today%E2%80%99s%20India%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22ht