p%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Two%20weeks%20after%20their%20first%20meeting%2C%20Indian%20and%20Maldivian%20senior%20officials%20have%20reached%20an%20understanding%20that%20India%20will%20%E2%80%9Creplace%E2%80%9D%20Indian%20military%20personnel%20who%20are%20operating%20one%20Dornier%20plane%20and%20two%20helicopters%20in%20the%20Indian%20ocean%20island%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20meeting%20of%20the%20core%20group%20that%20was%20to%20decide%20on%20the%20fate%20of%20the%20Indian%20military%20personnel%20was%20held%20in%20New%20Delhi%20on%20Friday%2C%20February%202.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20meeting%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforeign.gov.mv%2Findex.php%2Fen%2Fmedia-center%2Fstatements%2Fstatement-by-foreign-minister-moosa-zameer-at-the-eu-indo-pacific-ministerial-forum-2024-stmt-5%5C%22%3Ethe%20Maldivian%20foreign%20ministry%20issued%20a%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CBoth%20sides%20agreed%20that%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20will%20replace%20the%20military%20personnel%20in%20one%20of%20the%20three%20aviation%20platform%20by%2010%20March%202024%2C%20and%20will%20complete%20replacing%20military%20personnel%20in%20the%20other%20two%20platforms%20by%2010%20May%202024.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F37511%2FFirst_meeting_of_the_IndiaMaldives_High_Level_Core_Group%5C%22%3EThe%20Indian%20external%20affair%E2%80%99s%20readout%3C%2Fa%3E%20did%20not%20give%20the%20details.%20It%20only%20stated%20that%20both%20countries%20had%20%E2%80%9Cagreed%20on%20a%20set%20of%20mutually%20workable%20solutions%20to%20enable%20continued%20operation%20of%20Indian%20aviation%20platforms%20that%20provide%20humanitarian%20and%20medvac%20services%20to%20the%20people%20of%20Maldives%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20from%20the%20Maldivian%20foreign%20ministry%20does%20not%20provide%20clarity%20on%20whether%20the%20Indian%20military%20will%20be%20replaced%20by%20civilians%2C%20who%20could%20even%20be%20ex-servicemen.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20certainly%20clear%20that%20the%20Dornier%20and%20two%20helicopters%20gifted%20by%20India%20would%20remain%20in%20Maldives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20rather%20positive%20outcome%20for%20Maldivian%20President%20Mohamed%20Muizzu%20who%20had%20asked%20India%20to%20withdraw%20all%20its%20military%20personnel%20operating%20the%20three%20aircraft%20in%20by%20March%2015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuizzu%E2%80%99s%20successful%20campaign%20in%20the%20Presidential%20polls%20was%20largely%20based%20on%20the%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98India%20Out%E2%80%99%20campaign.%20Began%20in%202020%20by%20former%20president%20Abdulla%20Yameen%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98India%20Out%E2%80%99%20campaign%20aimed%20to%20corner%20the%20ruling%20Solih%20administration%20for%20his%20close%20links%20to%20New%20Delhi%20by%20claiming%20that%20presence%20of%20Indian%20military%20personnel%20was%20a%20violation%20of%20Maldivian%20sovereignty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20day%20after%20taking%20the%20oath%20of%20office%2C%20President%20Mohamed%20Muizzu%20of%20Maldives%20officially%20requested%20India%20to%20withdraw%20its%20troops%20from%20the%20country.%20When%20he%20met%20with%20the%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20in%20Dubai%2C%20both%20argeed%20to%20set%20up%20a%20committee%20of%20officials%20to%20discuss%20the%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Muizzu%20gave%20the%20ultimatum%20of%20March%2015%20at%20the%20first%20meeting%20of%20the%20committee%20last%20month%2C%20it%20was%20clear%20that%20Maldives%20did%20not%20want%20India%20to%20drag%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20Maldives%20set%20to%20go%20for%20parliamentary%20elections%20next%20month%2C%20the%20prospect%20of%20an%20imminent%20removal%20of%20Indian%20military%20troops%20will%20certainly%20boost%20his%20party%E2%80%99s%20election%20hopes.%20Currently%2C%20Muizzu%20is%20facing%20difficulties%20in%20getting%20his%20ministers%20endorsed%20from%20the%20MDP-dominated%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706897473000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F14103358%2FGDvFFVLbgAAmZK2.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-to-replace-military-personnel-operating-aircraft-helicopters-maldives%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20second%20meeting%20of%20the%20core%20group%20from%20two%20countries%20that%20was%20to%20decide%20on%20the%20fate%20of%20the%20Indian%20military%20personnel%20was%20held%20in%20New%20Delhi%20on%20Friday%2C%20February%202.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-to-replace-military-personnel-operating-aircraft-helicopters-maldives%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Several%20killed'%20as%20US%20airstrikes%20hit%2085%20targets%20in%20Iraq%20and%20Syria%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706896560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F02%2F70x70%2Fskynews-b-1-bomber-us-air-force_6442499.jpg%3F20240202222632%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fus-launches-retaliatory-strikes-in-response-to-jordan-attack-13062379%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20US%20military%20has%20launched%20an%20air%20assault%20on%20at%20least%2085%20targets%20in%20Iraq%20and%20Syria%20used%20by%20Iranian-backed%20militias%20on%20Friday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A632%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fus-launches-retaliatory-strikes-in-response-to-jordan-attack-13062379%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fus-launches-retaliatory-strikes-in-response-to-jordan-attack-13062379%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fus-launches-retaliatory-strikes-in-response-to-jordan-attack-13062379%2