5Bthe%5D%201980s%20and%201990s%20Mucormycosis%20was%20increasingly%20seen%20among%20immunocompromised%20individuals.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%20The%20term%20Mucormycosis%2C%20however%2C%20was%20first%20coined%20by%20American%20pathologist%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjama%2Farticle-abstract%2F320257%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERD%20Baker%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%201950s.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20at%20IIT-M%20has%20joined%20hands%20with%20ZorioX%20Innovation%20Labs%2C%20a%20Chennai-based%20medical%20equipment%20manufacturing%20startup%2C%20to%20organise%20around%2065%20implants%20for%20patients%20from%20economically-weaker%20sections.%20This%20initiative%20is%20based%20on%20metal%203D%20printing%20or%20additive%20manufacturing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20sits%20down%20with%20the%20minds%20behind%20this%20thoughtful%20venture%20to%20understand%20its%20scope%20in%20depth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EDangers%20of%20the%20deadly%20black%20fungus%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20an%20August%202023%20paper%20published%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC10168193%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJournal%20of%20Medical%20Mycology%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Gregoire%20Pasquier%2C%20%E2%80%9CMucormycosis%20is%20a%20rare%20opportunistic%20infection%20caused%20by%20a%20filamentous%20fungus%20belonging%20to%20the%20Mucorales%20order%E2%80%A6The%20diagnosis%20is%20difficult%20and%20consequently%2C%20it%20is%20often%20delayed%2C%20resulting%20in%20high%20lethality%20despite%20appropriate%20antifungal%20and%20surgical%20treatment.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20the%20second%20wave%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F267348%2Fomicron-india-covid-update-karnataka-genome-surveillance-committee%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECOVID-19%3C%2Fa%3E%20pandemic%20in%202021%20led%20to%20an%20upsurge%20in%20mucormycosis%20cases%20known%20as%20Covid-19-associated%20mucormycosis%20or%20CAM.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndian%20media%2C%20based%20on%20statements%20by%20members%20of%20the%20Indian%20government%2C%20reported%2011%2C717%20CAM%20cases%20on%20May%2025%2C%2028%2C252%20CAM%20cases%20on%20June%207%2C%2045%2C274%20CAM%20cases%20(including%204332%20deaths)%20on%20July%2020%2C%20and%2051%2C775%20CAM%20cases%20on%20November%2029%2C%202021%2C%E2%80%9D%20notes%20Pasquier.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20precise%20data%20were%20available%20because%20on%20May%2020%2C%202021%2C%20mucormycosis%20became%20a%20notifiable%20disease%20under%20the%20Epidemic%20Diseases%20Act%201897.%20Before%20this%20epidemic%2C%20mucormycosis%20was%20considered%20a%20rare%20opportunistic%20infection%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20particularly%20devastating%20effect%20of%20this%20disease%20is%20the%20loss%20of%20facial%20features%20which%20can%20have%20a%20debilitating%20effect%20on%20a%20patient%E2%80%99s%20mental%20health.%20The%20fungus%20responsible%20for%20mucormycosis%20can%20invade%20the%20tissues%20of%20the%20face%2C%20causing%20necrosis%20and%20disfigurement.%20In%20severe%20cases%2C%20patients%20can%20lose%20their%20eyes%2C%20nose%2C%20or%20even%20their%20entire%20face.%20The%20loss%20of%20these%20vital%20organs%20can%20seriously%20impact%20a%20patient%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20perform%20basic%20functions%20like%20breathing%2C%20eating%2C%20and%20communicating.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FIIT-Madras-Black-Fungus-Image-4-1706014757.jpg%5C